utilities
Class Tile

java.lang.Object
  utilities.Tile

public class Tile
extends java.lang.Object

This class provides the functionality of a tile, specific for different zones of interest to the robot. In this case, the only functionality of tile is to document the red and green zones of the robot. It contains the two beamed over coordinates stored as Point objects (as specified by the bluetooth connection) and an array of points that define the edges of the tile.

Method Detail

withinProximityOfTile

public char[] withinProximityOfTile(Position pos,
                                    double distance)
Calculates if the robot (or otherwise another Position object) is within a distance of the tile.

The return of this object is a character array with the data that will be processed elsewhere.

Parameters:
pos - The position object to compare against.
distance - The distance to calculate against.
Returns:
A character array containing the results. The first element in the character array contains whether the robot is within the distance of the tile or not ('y' and 'n' respectively). The second element in the character array contains which edge based on the first letter of its name (Left = 'l', Right = 'r', Top = 'u', Bottom = 'b').

computeSize

private double[] computeSize()
Computes the size of the array object. The first element is the x element and the second element returned is the y element.

Returns:
The dimensions of the tile.

computeAvoidanceTrajectory

public Point[] computeAvoidanceTrajectory(Position pos,
                                          char[] ch,
                                          int distance)
This method computes the avoidance trajectory of the robot based on a position. It is assumed the Position object input is the current position of the robot. However, it could be any object.

Parameters:
pos - A Position object to compare against.
ch - The side the tile detected. This greatly influences what path is taken.
distance - The distance the robot should remain from the tile (used for safety purposes).
Returns:
An array of Point's that must be taken by the robot to avoid the tile.
